overview: "The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification. The assistant analyzed the
  existing codebase against these requirements, identifying several gaps. A
  structured plan was then created and approved by the user. Subsequently, the
  assistant implemented two high-priority items from the plan: a 1-10 severity
  scale for tiredness interference, including critical safety warnings in both
  the questionnaire and the generated PDF report, and the detection and specific
  recommendations for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA). These changes
  involved updating data types, validation schemas, UI components, and report
  generation logic to enhance the questionnaire's diagnostic capabilities and
  user guidance."
